OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FPope Francis, 86, to have  
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fabdominal surgery          
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Pope Francis will have surgery on his  
OL,6, abdomen on Wednesday afternoon at      
OL,7, Rome's Gemelli hospital.               
OL,9,FHe is expected to stay in hospital for 
OL,10,F"several days" to recover from the     
OL,11,Fhernia operation, the Vatican said.    
OL,13,FThe hernia is "causing recurrent,      
OL,14,Fpainful and worsening" symptoms, added 
OL,15,FVatican spokesman Matteo Bruni.        
OL,17,FThe 86-year-old has faced a series of  
OL,18,Fhealth issues in recent years, and uses
OL,19,Fa cane and a wheelchair due to a       
OL,20,Fpersistent knee ailment.               
